'''Arriens Glacier''' ({{coord|73|27|48|S|68|24|1|E|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a small [[Antarctic]] [[glacier]], south of [[Casey Point]] in the [[Mawson Escarpment]], flowing west to reach [[Lambert Glacier]]. It was plotted from [[ANARE]] [[Aerial photography|aerial photographs]] taken in 1956, 1960 and 1973, and named by the [[Australian Antarctic Names and Medals Committee]] after P. Arriens, [[geochronologist]] with the ANARE [[Prince Charles Mountains]] survey party in 1973.
