'''Filippo De Palma''' (1813 – after 1873) was an Italian scientific instrument maker.

Scientific-instrument maker active in [[Naples]] in the third quarter of the nineteenth century. Exhibited in Paris in 1867 and in [[Vienna]] in 1873. Known to have produced electrical machines and physics instruments.

