Sir '''George Lindor Brown''' (9 February 1903, [[Liverpool]] – 22 February 1971) was an [[England|English]] [[physiologist]] and secretary of the [[Royal Society]], of which he was elected a [[Fellow of the Royal Society|Fellow]] in 1946.

He was commonly referred to as Sir Lindor Brown; by his own preference.

He was [[Waynflete Professorships|Waynflete Professor of Physiology]] at the University of Oxford from 1960 to 1967. He resigned from this post to become Principal of [[Hertford College]].

