'''Holmes''' is an [[impact crater]] in the [[Mare Australe quadrangle]] of [[Mars]], located at 75.0°S latitude and 293.2°W longitude. It is 122.0 &nbsp;km in diameter and was named after [[Arthur Holmes]], and the name was approved in 1973 by the International Astronomical Union (IAU) [[Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature]] (WGPSN).<ref>{{cite web|title=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature {{!}} Holmes|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/2544|website=usgs.gov|publisher=[[International Astronomical Union]]|accessdate=4 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.google.com/mars/|title=Google Mars|work=google.com}}</ref>
<gallery class="center" widths="190px" heights="180px" > Wikiholmeseast.jpg|East side of '''Holmes (crater)''', as seen by CTX camera (on [[Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter]]). </gallery>
