{{refimprove|date=March 2017}}

'''Nano aquariums''' are [[aquarium]]s with the emphasis on small scale inhabitants inside smaller sized aquariums. They can be either freshwater nano aquariums or saltwater nano aquariums. Nano fish species <ref>{{Cite web|title = List of nano fish species|url=http://thefishdoctor.co.uk/nano/nano-fish-nano-aquarium/|website = thefishdoctor.co.uk|accessdate = 2015-11-28}}</ref>   are chosen from any smaller sized species of [[tropical fish]]. Other possible inhabitants are freshwater and seawater [[shrimp]]s. Any plants for a nano aquarium also have to be of the smaller species.
The marine nano aquarium is more difficult to maintain than the nano freshwater aquarium. <ref>{{Cite web|title = nano marine aquarium|url=http://thefishdoctor.co.uk/aquarium-set-up/nano-marine-aquarium/|website = thefishdoctor.co.uk|accessdate = 2015-11-28}}</ref> 

